Full Description: Soles4Souls is a non-profit institution dedicated to fighting the devastating impact and perpetuation of poverty. The organization advances its anti-poverty mission by collecting new and used shoes and clothes from individuals, schools, faith-based institutions, civic organizations, and corporate partners, then distributing those shoes and clothes both via direct donations to people in need, and by provisioning qualified micro-enterprise programs designed to create jobs in poor and disadvantaged communities.  Through the collection and sale of used (and new) clothing and shoes, Soles4Souls helps create self-sustaining jobs that generate desperately needed revenues throughout those communities. The sale of footwear and apparel to support micro-jobs also provides the majority of funding to sustain Soles4Souls operations and further expand its donations of new shoes, and clothing. Soles4Souls was founded in 2006 and is based in Old Hickory, Tennessee.

Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: LaViano Jewelers operates as jewelers like Harry Winston did 30-50 years ago.  We secure special and extremely rare gemstones such as rare GIA certified diamonds, to natural Ceylon sapphires, to precious tsavorite and then create a unique design to compliment the stone. Full Description: What is an Upper Cervical Chiropractor? An upper cervical chiropractor is a specialized healthcare professional who focuses on the relationship between your spine’s upper two vertebrae and your overall health. The top two vertebrae are called the atlas and the axis, and they’re closely connected to the brain stem that allows your brain to communicate with the rest of your body.  Upper cervical chiropractors differ from general chiropractors in that they focus on the top two vertebrae instead of working on the entire spine and broader spinal manipulations. By using precise, gentle techniques, an Upper Cervical Chiropractor works to restore spinal alignment, alleviate pressure, and improve the function of the central nervous system.

Description: Redmatch delivers technologically advanced and robust SaaS solutions that maximize recruiting efficiency and place HR practitioners.
Full Description: Redmatch was established in the year 2000 and they are proud to be one of the leading HR Recruiting Software and Applicant Tracking System.  Their technology offers an innovative SaaS  solution with a unique matching technology to support the entire corporate recruitment and hiring lifecycle.  With many years of online recruiting experience, Redmatch goal is to provide any size organization from small and up to enterprise level a solution to allow them to streamline and automate the entire recruitment process. Redmatch unique matching technology eliminates the need to sift through irrelevant candidate profiles and resumes, and it enables recruiters to focus their time and effort only on those who are relevant. Their system calculates and rates the connection between a job seeker’s profile, the job seeker’s preferences and the position requirements, and it provides in real time a list of candidates who best match the position criteria. This significantly shortens the recruitment process.  The combination of the unique matching algorithm, a highly configurable platform and a wide selection of reporting tools, provides the recruiter with a complete solution to keep their organization ahead of the competition. With worldwide footprint Redmatch serves today many companies, recruiting agencies and job seekers with the distinctive cloud based recruitment solutions. The Redmatch technology has already matched millions of candidates with millions of open positions. Their system has been deployed in organizations around the world; including North America, India, Singapore, Canada, Australia, Israel, Hong Kong, Malaysia and Thailand, among others. Their experienced leadership team combines decades of work with recruitment companies, employers and job seekers to allow first-hand learning about the problems encountered by each of these crucial players. Through this experience, they designed the solution to face the challenge of recruiting the right people quickly and cost effectively.

And the important thing is that this is built on a well established business model - virtual goods and product placement.  When the teenager goes to the prom, she has the opportunity to spend a few credits to get the really nice dress that "upgrades" the story.  We are basically doing for storytelling what Zynga did for gaming - same market size, same proven revenue stream, only we have characters that people want posting to their wall, as opposed to messages about virtual farm animals.
